\- scope comes entirely from @name / name@ pairs.
   indentation is cosmetic — for the reader, never the parser. -\

\- flat -\

@chapter
@aside Keepers do. aside@
He read the letter twice.
chapter@

\- indented — parses identically to the above -\

@chapter
    @aside Keepers do. aside@
    He read the letter twice.
chapter@

\- mixed — also fine -\

@chapter
  @scene
The bell began to ring.
  scene@
chapter@
